The paper discusses a method for writing and verifying requirements for embedded software, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The proposed approach involves writing requirements in the programming language itself, which relates to programming languages (cs.PL) and embedded systems (cs.EM). The use of Design by Contract and Hoare-style assertions also suggests a focus on logic and verification (cs.LO), while the application to a specific industrial example highlights the relevance to engineering and technology (cs.ET).
